TITLE: Making XMLHttpRequest in Scala.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the Scala.js equivalent of the JavaScript ES6 code for creating an XMLHttpRequest, setting up a GET request to the Twitter API, handling the response, and updating the DOM with parsed tweets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/sjs-for-js/index.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
val xhr = new XMLHttpRequest()

xhr.open("GET",
  "https://api.twitter.com/1.1/search/" +
  "tweets.json?q=%23scalajs"
)
xhr.onload = { (e: Event) =>
  if (xhr.status == 200) {
    val r = JSON.parse(xhr.responseText)
    $("#tweets").html(parseTweets(r))
  }
}
xhr.send()
```

