TITLE: Higher-Order Functions Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Shows implementation of higher-order functions for calculating minimum and maximum values using custom extractors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/sjs-for-js/es6-to-scala-part3.md#2025-04-20_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function minmaxBy(arr, f) {
  return arr.reduce(
    ([min, max], e) => {
      const v = f(e);
      return [Math.min(min, v), Math.max(max, v)]
    }, 
    [Number.MAX_VALUE, Number.MIN_VALUE]
  )
}
```

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
def minmaxBy[T](seq: Seq[T], f: T => Int): (Int, Int) = {
  seq.foldLeft((Int.MaxValue, Int.MinValue)) {
    case ((min, max), e) =>
      val v = f(e)
      (math.min(min, v), math.max(max, v))
  }
}
```

