TITLE: Creating a Double Value Input Component in Laminar with Scala.js
DESCRIPTION: This component creates an input field for Double values with bidirectional data binding. It handles string-to-double parsing and formatting, maintaining a local String representation of the numeric value while synchronizing with an external Signal and Observer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/tutorial/laminar.md#2025-04-20_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
def inputForDouble(valueSignal: Signal[Double],
    valueUpdater: Observer[Double]): Input =
  val strValue = Var[String]("")
  input(
    typ := "text",
    value <-- strValue.signal,
    onInput.mapToValue --> strValue,
    valueSignal --> strValue.updater[Double] { (prevStr, newValue) =>
      if prevStr.toDoubleOption.contains(newValue) then prevStr
      else newValue.toString
    },
    strValue.signal --> { valueStr =>
      valueStr.toDoubleOption.foreach(valueUpdater.onNext)
    },
  )
end inputForDouble
```

