TITLE: Handling Optional Values with Undefined in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates a common pattern for handling optional parameters using `undefined`. The `log` function accepts an optional `context` parameter and uses an `if` statement to check if it's `undefined` before constructing the log message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/sjs-for-js/es6-to-scala-part1.md#2025-04-20_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function log(msg, context) {
  let s;
  if (context !== undefined)
    s = `[${context}] ${msg}`;
  else
    s = msg;
  console.log(s);
};

// produces: First message
log("First message");
// produces: [debug] Second message
log("Second message", "debug");
```

