TITLE: Regex with Post-processing for Precise Newline Handling
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use a regular expression with additional logic to handle newline characters precisely, avoiding matches between CR and LF characters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/regular-expressions.md#2025-04-20_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
def isBetweenCRAndNL(i: Int): Boolean =
  i > 0 && i < input.length() && input.charAt(i - 1) == '\r' && input.charAt(i) == '\n'

for {
  m <- regex3.findAllMatchIn(input)
  if !isBetweenCRAndNL(m.start(1)) && !isBetweenCRAndNL(m.end(1))
} {
  println(m.group(1))
}
```

