TITLE: Configuring Scala.js for WebAssembly Backend in sbt
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to enable the WebAssembly backend and configure Node.js flags in an sbt build file. It sets up the Scala.js linker config to use WebAssembly and ES modules, and configures Node.js with experimental flags for Wasm support.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/project/webassembly.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
// Emit ES modules with the Wasm backend
scalaJSLinkerConfig := {
  scalaJSLinkerConfig.value
    .withExperimentalUseWebAssembly(true) // use the Wasm backend
    .withModuleKind(ModuleKind.ESModule)  // required by the Wasm backend
},

// Configure Node.js (at least v23) to support the required Wasm features
jsEnv := {
  val config = NodeJSEnv.Config()
    .withArgs(List(
      "--experimental-wasm-exnref", // required
      "--experimental-wasm-imported-strings", // optional (good for performance)
      "--turboshaft-wasm", // optional, but significantly increases stability
    ))
  new NodeJSEnv(config)
},
```

