TITLE: Implementing Traits with Classes in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to implement traits (mixin pattern) using ES6 classes and `Object.assign`.  It defines a `Circle` class extending `Shape` and a `Clickable` object that is mixed into a `ClickableCircle` class. The `Object.assign` method is used to copy the properties and methods of the `Clickable` object to the `ClickableCircle` prototype.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/sjs-for-js/es6-to-scala-part1.md#2025-04-20_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class Circle extends Shape {
  constructor(x, y, r) {
    super(x, y);
    this.r = r;
  }

  draw() {
    console.log(`Circle at ${this.x}, ${this.y} with radius ${this.r}`);
  }
}

const Clickable = {
  onClick() {
    console.log("Clicked!");
  }
};

class ClickableCircle extends Circle {}
Object.assign(ClickableCircle.prototype, Clickable);

const cc = new ClickableCircle(0, 0, 42);
cc.onClick();
```

