TITLE: Configuring Scala.js WebAssembly Backend Settings
DESCRIPTION: Configuration code for enabling the experimental WebAssembly backend in Scala.js and setting up Node.js environment with required WebAssembly features. Includes settings for module type and Node.js arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/_posts/news/2024-09-28-announcing-scalajs-1.17.0.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
// Emit ES modules with the Wasm backend
scalaJSLinkerConfig := {
  scalaJSLinkerConfig.value
    .withExperimentalUseWebAssembly(true) // use the Wasm backend
    .withModuleKind(ModuleKind.ESModule)  // required by the Wasm backend
},

// Configure Node.js (at least v22) to support the required Wasm features
jsEnv := {
  val config = NodeJSEnv.Config()
    .withArgs(List(
      "--experimental-wasm-exnref", // required
      "--experimental-wasm-imported-strings", // optional (good for performance)
      "--turboshaft-wasm", // optional, but significantly increases stability
    ))
  new NodeJSEnv(config)
},
```

