TITLE: Overloading Method with Recursive Call Issue in Scala.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet presents a problematic method overload that leads to infinite recursion when called. It highlights the issues that can arise when methods are not mutually exclusive in their definitions, particularly when using run-time type resolution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/doc/interoperability/sjs-defined-js-classes.md#2025-04-20_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
// @ScalaJSDefined
class Foo extends js.Object {
  def bar(x: String): String = bar(x: Any)
  def bar(x: Any): String = "bar " + x
}

val foo = new Foo
println(foo.bar("world")) // infinite recursion
```

