TITLE: Demonstrating Constructor this Usage Restriction in Scala
DESCRIPTION: Example showing a code pattern that is now restricted in Scala.js 1.18.1, where using 'this' before super constructor calls in try-catch blocks is no longer allowed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js-website/blob/main/_posts/news/2025-01-09-announcing-scalajs-1.18.1.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
class Parent(val i: Int)

class Child extends Parent({
  val p = try Integer.parseInt("foo") catch { case _: NumberFormatException => 42 }
  p
})

object Test {
  def main(args: Array[String]): Unit =
    println(new Child().i)
}
```
